2020 was rough for me. Transitioning out of a toxic job & relationship. I was constantly questioning myself and my choices... Questioning why in the hell I made my big move, giving up a life in Hawaii I spent years building. Wondering if I'll always feel like the grass is greener on the other side...
I still don't have everything figured out, needless to say, but I'm doing better than I was, and that's what counts. Take this as a reminder, from me to you... not to be so hard on yourself. It's something I have to remind myself of constantly. You may not be EXACTLY where you want to be, but you aren't where you WERE, and sometimes that's all that matters. 🫶

My most frequently asked questions are regarding my tattoos. What do they mean? What's my fav, etc. I figured I would start giving you guys more of a backstory about some of them. These are my two newest finished pieces. Would you believe me if I told you they were coverups?! Both previous pieces were reminders from toxic past relationships that gave me the ick every time I looked at them. Don't get me wrong, I absolutely do not regret my tattoos, I just wish some of them had been more thought out haha but i guess that's what you get for starting your heavily tattooed journey at 17 getting blasted in a strangers garage by someone's cousin 😂 Any questions you've been dying to ask? I'll do my best to get back/video respond to each and every one 🥰

As some of you know, I was adopted at birth. 
I was raised in an open adoption, so I've known my biological family my entire life. In my opinion, this was an incredibly selfless decision that my adoptive parents made. I feel so incredibly blessed in so many ways and of course this is one of them. 
Though our relationship looks perfect, it wasn't always. I was a complete sh*thead as a teenager, I'm sure some/many of you can relate to that. 
I like to think everything that we've been through, has only made our relationship stronger but of course it's hard not to guilt trip yourself for certain parts of your past. That good ol what doesn't kill ya makes ya stronger philosophy 🍻 
Anyways. cheers to all you moms out there, (mine especially hehe) keep your head up- you're doing an absolutely incredible job, just in case no one has told you lately ❤️
